1.=> DDL (Data Definition Language)
Database & table structure create, change, delete panna use pannura commands.

Database and table structure handling

Columns, constraints, data types maintain pannurathu

Data ah illa, table structure mela work

One English sentence:
â€œDDL commands are used to define and modify the structure of a database.â€



ğŸ“Œ DDL Commands â€“ Correct Spelling


| Command  | Correct Spelling | Tamil Meaning                               |
| -------- | ---------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| CREATE   | Create           | Database/Table create                       |
| ALTER    | Alter            | Structure change (add column etc.)          |
| DROP     | Drop             | Database/Table delete (permanently)         |
| TRUNCATE | Truncate         | Table data full-ah delete, structure remain |
| RENAME   | Rename           | Table name change                           |
| COMMENT  | Comment          | Table/column-ku description add             |



DDL focuses only on the structure of the database and tables.
It manages tables, columns, and constraints.
DDL commands are used for creating, modifying, and deleting database structures




